aki_risk_factors: 肌酐升高, 少尿, 低血压, 心动过速
full_prompt:
As a nephrology specialist, assess the patient's risk of developing acute kidney injury (AKI) based on the following clinical data:
Patient Information:
- Age: 78 years
- Gender: Female

Key Lab Indicators:
- Baseline Creatinine: 0.7 μmol/L
- Maximum Creatinine: 2.8 μmol/L
- Creatinine Change: 300.0% from baseline
- Creatinine Trend: 0.005 μmol/L/hour

Vital Signs:
- Minimum Mean Arterial Pressure: 47.0 mmHg
- Maximum Heart Rate: 136 beats/min

Urine Output:
- 6-hour Urine Output: 87.0 ml
- 24-hour Urine Output: 197.0 ml
- Urine Output Rate: 8.2 ml/hour
- Urine Output per kg: 0.131 ml/kg/hour

Risk Assessment:
Creatinine elevation: 300.0% above baseline (AKI criteria)
Severe oliguria: <0.5ml/kg/hr (AKI Stage 3)
Hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <65mmHg (renal hypoperfusion)
Tachycardia: Heart rate >120 bpm (volume depletion)
Critical oliguria: <0.3ml/kg/hr (high risk)
Severe hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <60mmHg (critical)
Composite Risk Score: 10...

As a nephrology specialist, assess the patient's risk of developing acute kidney injury (AKI) based on the following clinical data:
Patient Information:
- Age: 64 years
- Gender: Male

Key Lab Indicators:
- Baseline Creatinine: 4.0 μmol/L
- Maximum Creatinine: 4.7 μmol/L
- Creatinine Change: 17.5% from baseline
- Creatinine Trend: 0.044 μmol/L/hour

Vital Signs:
- Minimum Mean Arterial Pressure: 22.0 mmHg
- Maximum Heart Rate: 127 beats/min

Urine Output:
- 6-hour Urine Output: 5.0 ml
- 24-hour Urine Output: 5.0 ml
- Urine Output Rate: 0.2 ml/hour
- Urine Output per kg: 0.002 ml/kg/hour

Risk Assessment:
Severe oliguria: <0.5ml/kg/hr (AKI Stage 3)
Hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <65mmHg (renal hypoperfusion)
Tachycardia: Heart rate >120 bpm (volume depletion)
Critical oliguria: <0.3ml/kg/hr (high risk)
Severe hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <60mmHg (critical)
Composite Risk Score: 7...

- Gender: Female

- Creatinine Change: 60.0% from baseline
- Creatinine Trend: 0.017 μmol/L/hour

Vital Signs:
- Minimum Mean Arterial Pressure: 33.0 mmHg
- Maximum Heart Rate: 160 beats/min

Urine Output:

- 24-hour Urine Output: 2355.0 ml

- Urine Output per kg: 1.504 ml/kg/hour

Risk Assessment:
Creatinine elevation: 60.0% above baseline (AKI criteria)
Hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <65mmHg (renal hypoperfusion)

Severe hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <60mmHg (critical)

As a nephrology specialist, assess the patient's risk of developing acute kidney injury (AKI) based on the following clinical data:
Patient Information:
- Age: 91 years
- Gender: Female

Key Lab Indicators:
- Baseline Creatinine: 0.1 μmol/L
- Maximum Creatinine: 2.3 μmol/L
- Creatinine Change: 1548.2% from baseline
- Creatinine Trend: 0.100 μmol/L/hour

Vital Signs:
- Minimum Mean Arterial Pressure: 38.0 mmHg
- Maximum Heart Rate: 81 beats/min

Urine Output:
- 6-hour Urine Output: 0.0 ml
- 24-hour Urine Output: 34.0 ml
- Urine Output Rate: 1.4 ml/hour
- Urine Output per kg: 0.023 ml/kg/hour

Risk Assessment:
Creatinine elevation: 1548.2% above baseline (AKI criteria)
Severe oliguria: <0.5ml/kg/hr (AKI Stage 3)
Hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <65mmHg (renal hypoperfusion)
Critical oliguria: <0.3ml/kg/hr (high risk)
Severe hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <60mmHg (critical)
Composite Risk Score: 8...

Vital Signs:

- Maximum Heart Rate: 141 beats/min

- 24-hour Urine Output: 1175.0 ml

Hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <65mmHg (renal hypoperfusion)

Severe hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <60mmHg (critical)

As a nephrology specialist, assess the patient's risk of developing acute kidney injury (AKI) based on the following clinical data:
Patient Information:
- Age: 53 years
- Gender: Female

Key Lab Indicators:
- Baseline Creatinine: 1.8 μmol/L
- Maximum Creatinine: 3.3 μmol/L
- Creatinine Change: 83.3% from baseline
- Creatinine Trend: -0.028 μmol/L/hour

Vital Signs:
- Minimum Mean Arterial Pressure: 53.0 mmHg
- Maximum Heart Rate: 137 beats/min

Urine Output:
- 6-hour Urine Output: 300.0 ml
- 24-hour Urine Output: 950.0 ml
- Urine Output Rate: 39.6 ml/hour
- Urine Output per kg: 0.540 ml/kg/hour

Risk Assessment:
Creatinine elevation: 83.3% above baseline (AKI criteria)
Hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <65mmHg (renal hypoperfusion)
Tachycardia: Heart rate >120 bpm (volume depletion)
Severe hypotension: Mean arterial pressure <60mmHg (critical)
Composite Risk Score: 7...
